docs.lead_paragraph: There has been some decrease in the death rate charged to the pneumonias, and to the infectious diseases, but in contrast to this trend there has been little change in the death rate charged to neo-natal deaths, including premature birth, injury at birth and other diseases peculiar to early infancy, Health Commissioner Shirley W. Wynne declared recently at a meeting at the New York Academy of Medicine.

headline.main: DEATH RATE HERE TAKES ANOTHER DROP,; Health Commissioner Wynne Points to Decrees in Deaths One to Pneumonia.
